# The per-agent pi-runtime image (packages/runtime/Dockerfile) builds with the repo
# ROOT as its context, because the runtime declares @houston/runtime-client via
# `file:../runtime-client` and the frozen install needs that sibling on disk.
# This trims the context tar to roughly what the Dockerfile actually COPYs.
# (Every other Docker build in the repo uses the .dockerignore at ITS OWN context
# root; this file only applies to root-context builds.)
**/node_modules
.git
**/target
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
.context
